body:
## Steps to reproduce the issue

``bash tests/tools/autotest.sh -v -n 10 -p prep test2.v`` fails on the following test case:

```
module test (din, dout);
        input   wire    [DIM_1*DIM_2-1:0] din;
        output  reg     [DIM_1*DIM_2-1:0] dout;

        integer i, j;
        parameter integer DIM_1 = 17;
        parameter integer DIM_2 = 7;

        reg [DIM_1-1:0] din_array  [DIM_2-1:0];
        reg [DIM_1-1:0] dout_array [DIM_2-1:0];

        always @* begin
                for (i = 0; i < DIM_2; i=i+1) begin
                        din_array[i] = din[DIM_1*i +: DIM_1];
                        dout[DIM_1*i +: DIM_1] = dout_array[i];
                end
        end

        always @* begin
                for (i = 0; i < DIM_2; i=i+1)
                        dout_array[i] = din_array[i];

                for (i = 0; i < DIM_2-1; i=i+3) begin
                        for (j = 0 ; j < DIM_1-1; j=j+1) begin
                                // WE THINK HERE IS THE BUG
                                {dout_array[i][j+1], dout_array[i][j]} = dout_array[i][j] + dout_array[i+1][j];
                        end
                end
        end
endmodule
```

## Expected behavior

Autotest fails not.

## Actual behavior

Autotest fails.

